article.headline: Dayton 31, Fordham 24
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Kevin Hoyng's 69-yard touchdown pass to Nick Ruhe with 5:44 left gave Dayton a 31-24 victory over Fordham on Saturday. Hoyng completed 15-of-28 for 261 yards and two TDs for the Flyers (4-0), who blew a 21-point lead but managed to pull out the win. Ruhe finished with three catches for 117 yards. John Skelton was 22-of-44 for 242 yards for the Rams (2-2), threw two interceptions and was sacked five times. The Rams, who trailed 24-3, made it 24-10 on Skelton's 17-yard touchdown pass to Jason Caldwell in the fourth quarter, then cut the lead to one TD on the quarterback's 33-yard scoring pass to Richard Raylon. Xavier Martin's 2-yard run at 6:50 of the fourth quarter tied the game before Hoyng threw his game-winner. Jack O'Dell's 10-yard run at 3:14 of the first quarter gave Dayton a 7-0 lead, and seven seconds into the second quarter Hoyng combined with Matt Champa on a 19-yard pass that boosted the lead to 14-0. Hoyng followed with an 18-yard TD pass to O'Dell at 3:13 for a 21-0 advantage. Adam Dariko's 30-yard field goal with 15 seconds to play cut the lead to 21-3. Matt Swartz responded with a 21-yard field goal lead early in the third quarter to give the Flyers a 24-3 lead.
